INSERT INTO news VALUES(650,'https://react.dev/blog/2023/03/22/react-labs-what-we-have-been-working-on-march-2023','React Labs: What We''ve Been Working On – March 2023','In React Labs posts, we write about projects in active research and development. We''ve made significant progress on them since our last update, and we''d like to share what we learned.','https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2023-03-22T00:00:00','React Blog','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(651,'https://react.dev/blog/2023/03/16/introducing-react-dev','Introducing react.dev','Today we are thrilled to launch react.dev, the new home for React and its documentation. In this post, we would like to give you a tour of the new site.','https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2023-03-16T00:00:00','React Blog','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(652,'https://react.dev/blog/2022/06/15/react-labs-what-we-have-been-working-on-june-2022','React Labs: What We''ve Been Working On – June 2022','React 18 was years in the making, and with it brought valuable lessons for the React team. Its release was the result of many years of research and exploring many paths. Some of those paths were successful; many more were dead-ends that led to new in','https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2022-06-15T00:00:00','React Blog','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(653,'https://react.dev/blog/2022/03/29/react-v18','React v18.0','React 18 is now available on npm! In our last post, we shared step-by-step instructions for upgrading your app to React 18. In this post, we''ll give an overview of what''s new in React 18, and what it means for the future.','https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2022-03-08T00:00:00','React Blog','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(654,'https://react.dev/blog/2022/03/08/react-18-upgrade-guide','How to Upgrade to React 18','As we shared in the release post, React 18 introduces features powered by our new concurrent renderer, with a gradual adoption strategy for existing applications. In this post, we will guide you through the steps for upgrading to React 18.','https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2022-03-08T00:00:00','React Blog','Frontend');
