INSERT INTO news VALUES(2756,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/193','#193 - Vue.js 3.1.0-beta Migration Build now available! Vue Devtools new beta supports Vue 2.x and more!',replace('Hi everyone,\n\nGreat news! [Vue v3.1.0-beta](https://github.com/vuejs/vue-next/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md) has been released with a set of new features and bug fixes, including the onServerPrefetch lifecycle hook!\n\nBut that’s not all, because v3.1 comes','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2021-05-10T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2757,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/192','#192 - Vue 3.0 to drop IE 11 support (RFC); 2 days until Vueconf.us; Component testing in Cypress;',replace('Hi there!\n\nLast month might not have been the most eventful when it comes to Vue news, but there’s been plenty of exciting new libraries for Vue 3.0. Those include:\n\n- [🍍Pinia](https://pinia.esm.dev/) – a new Vuex alternative created by Eduardo San M','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2021-04-12T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2758,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/191','#191 - State of Vue 2021, Vite v2 released; Vuex 5 RFC; Vuetify for Vue 3 in alpha and more!',replace('Welcome back!\n\nThose last 3 weeks have been truly crazy! First of all, [Evan’s State of Vuenion 2021 talk at Vue.js Amsterdam](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=El8Jw2CFj7g) where he is covering the recent developments in the Vue ecosystem. How Vue is ','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2021-03-06T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2759,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/190','#190 - Vuex 4.0.0 is here! 🚀 New Vite docs and dedicated Discord sever; Vue Contributor days and more!',replace('Hi everyone,\n\nGreat news! [Vuex 4.0.0 (stable)](https://github.com/vuejs/vuex/releases/tag/v4.0.0) for Vue 3.0 has been finally released! This is the version of Vuex that is 99% backward compatible with the old Vuex (v3) that you might be currently u','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2021-02-10T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2760,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/189','#189 - Reflections for 2020-2021; Vue-Storefront raises $1.5M; Element UI for Vue 3.0 and more!',replace('Hey there!\n\nWelcome, to the first issue of 2021!\n\nThe Vue.js blog has been reactivated and can be found at [blog.vuejs.org](https://blog.vuejs.org/). There’s a new article posted – [Reflections for 2020-2021](https://blog.vuejs.org/posts/hello-2021.h','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2021-01-24T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2761,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/188','#188 - Enjoy the Vuelidays! And a happy new year! 🎉',replace('Hey everyone,\n\nhope you had a great time during the holiday season! 🌲 I know I had! 🥟 🐕\n\nLet’s start with some great news. [Guillaume Chau](https://twitter.com/Akryum) has published a new beta release of the [Vue.js Devtools v6](https://twitter.com/A','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2020-12-29T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2762,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/187','#187 - The Vue.js Newsletter is back! 🎉',replace('Hey there,\n\nit’s been a while... Did you miss the newsletter? I hope you did actually! I’m sorry for the unexpected break. And trust me, getting myself to send this issue, was harder with every week that passed. 2020 has been pretty rough for all of ','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2020-12-13T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2763,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/186','#186 - 🍰 Vue.js v3.0.0 "One Piece" Released! 🎉  The State of Nuxt.js and more!',replace('Hello!\n\nThe time is now! Vue.js v3.0, codename "__One Piece__" has just been officially released! 🎉 Watch the [announcement talk by Evan You](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Vp5ANvd88x0)!\n\nThis is a huge milestone for us that, to quote Evan You himse','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2020-09-18T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2764,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/185','#185 - Vue-CLI v4.5.0 ships with built-in Vue 3.0 support; Nuxt v2.14 released; VueConf Toronto announced!',replace('Hello Vuers,\n\nwith the newly released [Vue-CLI v4.5.x](https://github.com/vuejs/vue-cli/releases/tag/v4.5.0), the CLI supports Vue 3.0 projects out of the box, without the need for the vue-cli-plugin-vue-next plugin. The author of the release – [Haoq','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2020-08-22T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2765,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/184','#184 - Vue.js 3.0 Release Candidate is here! 3.0 Docs in beta; Vue-Devtools beta for Vue 3.0 available and more!',replace('👋 Hi there,\n\ngreat news! We are now closer than ever to the official Vue 3.0 release. The first Release Candidate marks the RC stage of the project which will be followed by a stable stage. You can read the whole announcement [here](https://github.co','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2020-07-22T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2766,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/183','#183 - Vue 3.0 status update; Svelte-inspired magic for Vue SFC; Nuxt.js v2.13 is out and more!',replace('Hi there,\n\nAs we are all waiting for the new major version of Vue, you might be wondering – how much longer? We are happy to share the latest [status update](https://github.com/vuejs/rfcs/issues/183) of the project.\n\n__TL;DR; Release Candidate mid Ju','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2020-07-05T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2767,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/182','#182 - Quasar.Conf coming online on July 5th; The process of rewriting Vue.js;',replace('Hi there,\n\nI’m back with some interesting news for you!\n\nAre you interested in Quasar? If yes, there’s an online [Quasar.Conf](https://dev.to/quasar/introducing-quasar-conf-52gg) coming on July, 5th. You can still submit your lightning talks if you w','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2020-06-15T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2768,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/181','#181 - #181: 📓 Big News from Nuxt.js – Introducing the Content and Components modules 🎉',replace('Hi there,\n\nwe’ve just had some incredibly exciting 2 weeks in the Nuxt.js world! First the Nuxt team released the [__components module__](https://github.com/nuxt/components), which allows you to skip importing Vue components manually as they will be ','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2020-05-24T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2769,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/180','#180 - 🏎 Say hi to Vite! A brand new, extremely fast development setup for Vue. So fast it feels instant!',replace('Hey there,\n\nAs you all know "*Vue*" in French stands for "*View*" and pretty much describes what Vue.js doing – handling the view part. This week, I’d like to introduce you to "*[Vite](https://github.com/vuejs/vite)*", which means "*Fast*". It’s a br','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2020-05-11T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2770,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/179','#179 - 🎉 Vue.js v3.0-beta released! Check out the new State of Vue update from Evan You; Great things for TS users coming in Vue 3.0!',replace('Hello,\n\nlong time no see... Sorry about that! Have you been missing the newsletter? I sure hope you did.\n\nI’ve got some exciting news for you! __Vue v3.0-beta has been released!__ This brings us yet another step closer to the final release. There’s a','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2020-04-19T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2771,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/178','#178 - Wikimedia adopting Vue! 🎉 New Vue online meetup initiatives and more videos from VueConf.us and Vue.js Amsterdam',replace('Hello,\n\nDo you know this website called Wikipedia? Where you can read about things? Like an online encyclopedia of sorts, but everyone can contribute? 🙃 It’s maintained by the good people from Wikimedia as well as volunteers and a few days ago the de','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2020-03-29T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2772,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/177','#177 - Updated Vue.js Roadmap; Vuex v4.0.0-alpha.1 has been released; Kia King Ishii join the core team; Nuxt v2.12 released; Videos from Vue.js Amsterdam 2020 are here!',replace('Hi there,\n\nit’s been a while since the last issue and I’m terribly sorry about that. The last few weeks have been really high on anxiety with all that’s been going on right now in the world. I hope you are all safe and healthy! 💚\n\nThere are some good','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2020-03-18T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2773,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/176','#176 - 🎉 Vue.js: The Documentary is here! VueConf.TO and Vue London announced; Using state machines with Vue and more!',replace('Hello!\n\nWhat a week it was! Sorry for skipping last week news – I’ve had so much fun at [Vue.js Amsterdam](https://vuejs.amsterdam/) (check out some of the photos [here](https://www.facebook.com/vuejsamsterdam/posts/622183358327862)) and truth be tol','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2020-02-27T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
