INSERT INTO news VALUES(2785,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/164','#164 - 9 RFCs are about to be finalised – last chance to provide feedback! Videos from ReactiveConf and more!','Hi everyone, it’s An here again. It’s been one of those more quiet weeks on the FE front (I know, I know), so we don’t have a lot to share this time. Still, there’s a couple of nice videos from ReactiveConf, interesting articles on Tailwind CSS and a','https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-11-07T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2786,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/163','#163 - Vue-Devtools v5.3.0 released! Articles on Vue 3.0 and more!','Hey everyone, it''s An here again freezing to death in this first wave of cold air from the Alps. From the core team, [Gillaume](https://twitter.com/akryum) is still on a roll, this time with a new version of [Vue Devtools](https://github.com/vuejs/vu','https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-10-30T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2787,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/162','#162 - Vue-Apollo v3.0 has been released and now becomes a part of the official libraries;',replace('Hello,\n\n[Guillaume](https://twitter.com/akryum) seems to have been very productive this week. Two new versions of his libraries have been released: [Vue-Apollo v3.0](https://github.com/vuejs/vue-apollo/releases/tag/v3.0.0) is here and has a new home ','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-10-24T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2788,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/161','#161 - Vue-CLI 4.0 released! VuePress v1.2 Released! Awesomejs.dev for Vue packages!',replace('Hello Vuegazers,\n\nI’m very happy to let you know that Vue has just passed the [magical 150k stargazers](https://github.com/vuejs/vue/stargazers) on GitHub. Remember to put on your sunglasses when the new shiny Vue release ships. 😎\n\nSpeaking of new re','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-10-16T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2789,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/160','#160 - Vue.js 3.0 source code is now public! Learn more about the upcoming changes;',replace('Hello,\n\nI’m happy to tell you that the Vue.js 3.0 [source code](https://github.com/vuejs/vue-next) has been made public and is now in the pre-alpha stage! 🔥 You can now take a peek at the beautiful TypeScript codebase and watch it grow every week unt','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-10-10T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2790,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/159','#159 - Nuxt.js v2.10.0 released along with a new homepage! Polish Vue Vixens chapter and more!',replace('Hello everybody,\n\nit''s An here this time with a massive [Oktoberfest](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oktoberfest) hangover (note to self: 3 liters of weißbier might be a little too much for an empty stomach).\n\nSome of you must already be at [Vue.js Lo','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-10-04T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2791,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/158','#158 - Quasar App CLI v1.1.0 released! New episode of Views On Vue and more!',replace('Hello,\n\nNot that much has happened this week, I guess everyone is preparing for [Vue.js London](https://vuejs.london/) next weekend (October 5-6). You might still get a ticket if you hurry up!\n\nThe [Quasar App CLI v1.1.0](https://medium.com/quasar-fr','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-09-26T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2792,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/157','#157 - Gridsome v0.7, VuePress v1.1.0 and  Bootstrap-Vue v2 released! "Looking into the Vueture" by Natalia Tepluhina and more!',replace('Hello,\n\nThis week is release week: VuePress, Gridsome and Bootstrap-Vue have been released (respectively versions 1.1.0, 0.7 and 2.0). 🎉\n\nAlso, if you would like to take a peek into the vueture check out the newest [talk by Natalia Tepluhina](https:/','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-09-18T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2793,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/156','#156 - Quasar v1.1.0 released! 11 talks from VueDay 2019 published; How to create the perfect docs;',replace('Hello everyone,\n\nI’m happy to let you know that [Quasar v1.1.0 has been released](https://forum.quasar-framework.org/topic/4234/quasar-1-1-0-released-new-component-qvirtualscroll-many-other-new-things-a-lot-of-improvements-and-fixes) with several new','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-09-05T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2794,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/155','#155 - Vue Community Guide is finally out! New releases: Vue-CLI v4.0-rc.0 and VeeValidate v3.0!',replace('Hello,\n\nWhen I first heard about the [Vue Community Guide](https://vue-community.org/) idea during the Vue.js Amsterdam conference I got really excited about it. A place where beginners could easily learn to navigate the vast Vue ecosystem, including','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-08-28T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2795,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/154','#154 - The Vue Function-based Component API RFC is back, now known as the Composition API 🎉 Nuxt.js v2.9.0 is out! Introducing NuxtPress and more!',replace('Hello,\n\nHere I got some amazing news for you!\n\nRemember the Function-based Component API proposal? After a long discussion and the feedback we collected from the community, it ended up rejected, but is now back, in a fully reworked form and is known ','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-08-20T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2796,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/153','#153 - Views on Vue with Debbie O’Brien; A tale of three users aka how to approach testing and more!',replace('Hello,\n\nThis has been a rather calm week when it comes to Vue-related news, but we still have some pretty neat tutorials for you to read.\n\nThere’s also a new interview with [Debbie O’Brien](https://twitter.com/debs_obrien) on the latest [Views on Vue','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-08-13T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2797,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/152','#152 - Vue-Router v3.1.0 released; Buefy v0.8.0 released; New examples on how to use the vue-function-api.',replace('Hello,\n\namazing news – the [Vue-Router v3.1.0](https://github.com/vuejs/vue-router/releases/tag/v3.1.0) has been released by [Posva](https://twitter.com/posva/) and along with several fixes and improvements, the Router-Link component now has a scoped','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-08-06T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2798,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/151','#151 - Join the VuePress core team! VueConf.us location and date announced and more!',replace('Hello,\n\nhave you thought about contributing to the Vue.js ecosystem? Do you know VuePress? [ULIVZ](https://twitter.com/_ulivz), the main maintainer is building a core team for it. Check out the [announcement post](https://github.com/vuejs/vuepress/is','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-07-30T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2799,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/150','#150 - Vuetify v2.0 "Arcadia" is here! 🎉 Two new podcast episodes with Natalia and Chris and more!',replace('Hello,\n\nhere’s something many of you have been waiting for – [Vuetify v2.0 has been officially released](https://github.com/vuetifyjs/vuetify/releases/tag/v2.0.0)! 🎉 Congrats on all the hard work to the Vuetify team! If you would like to say thanks t','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-07-23T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2800,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/149','#149 - How to create Typeform-like forms in Vue; How to use Vue Function API today; Introduction to slots in Vue and more!',replace('Hello,\n\nthis week has been pretty calm in terms of news, but definitely not when it comes to interesting articles and tutorials. One of my fav authors – [Krutie Patel](https://twitter.com/KrutiePatel) is now blogging for Vue Mastery and has just publ','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-07-16T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2801,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/148','#148 - Evan You talks about Framework Design; Support the Vue Newsletter; Try out the Vue 3.0 Function API RFC and more',replace('Hello,\n\nhave you been wondering how front-end frameworks are being designed? Evan You had recently given a pretty [great talk at JSConf.Asia](https://www.youtube.com/watch?utm_campaign=Vue.js+News&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_source=Revue+newsletter&','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-07-09T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2802,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/147','#147 - Vue Function API discussion, VueAndWine workshosp and VueCamp!',replace('Welcome back,\n\nIf you are still worried about the recent function API RFC – please don’t! We heard your feedback and we’re grateful for it! 🙌 __Please know that there are no plans to ever deprecate the object-based API__. We’re also working on a new ','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-07-02T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2803,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/146','#146 - Vue.js London Workshop tickets are on sale! How to upgrade your VuePress site and more!',replace('Hello,\n\nGreat news for everyone in Europe looking for some quality Vue workshops. Vue.js London has [announced 6 awesome workshops](https://vuejs.london/workshops) to take place on Saturday, October 5th, the day after the conference.\n\nI feel that rec','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-06-18T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2804,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/145','#145 - Function-based Component API RFC; VuePress v1.x published and more!',replace('Hello,\n\nprobably the biggest RFC in Vue’s history has been published this week – the [function-based component API](https://github.com/vuejs/rfcs/blob/function-apis/active-rfcs/0000-function-api.md). It’s a huge step towards better composability and ','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-06-11T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2805,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/144','#144 - Nuxt.js v2.8 is out ✨ Is Vue suddenly getting very mainstream? 🤷‍♂️ The Paradox of Abstraction and more!',replace('Hello,\n\nI hope you had a great week. For us, the week was full or surprises. If you’re using Netflix, you might have seen a new series, where the main character is [using Vue to build the web app to sell certain *things* online](https://twitter.com/v','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-06-04T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2806,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/143','#143 - All VueConf.US talks available; Vue 3.0: Abandoning the Class Syntax; What’s next for Nuxt?',replace('Hello,\n\nI hope you had a great weekend!\n\nLast week we had some pretty significant decisions made in the core team – namely to drop the Class API syntax for Vue 3.0. Don’t feel sad though, the TypeScript support will still be pretty amazing – we care ','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-05-28T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2807,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/142','#142 - Nuxt v2.7.0 is out! 🎉 VueConfTO tickets on sale and first batch of speakers announced. 🇨🇦',replace('Hello,\nGreat news Nuxt fans! [Nuxt v2.7](https://github.com/nuxt/nuxt.js/releases/tag/v2.7.0) has been released and it comes with some pretty amazing improvements. For example, using a calling console.log inside your application during SSR will still','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-05-22T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2808,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/141','#141 -  Vetur 0.20.0 released. Gridsome 0.6 is here. jQuery, NativeScript and...',replace('Hello!\n\nThere is quite a spread of articles this week that should be of interest to a variety of skill level. From migrating to Vue from jQuery to building component libraries with Lerna, Storybook, and npm.\n\nWe also have a couple of new releases: Ve','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-05-15T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2809,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/140','#140 - Vuex v3.1.1 released. Vue-CLI v4.0-alpha is here; Managing state with Apollo and more!',replace('Hello!\n\nWhoa, there is so much content this week we had a really hard time picking up the articles (some of them might show up next week).\n\nFirst of all, [Vuex got a new release](https://github.com/vuejs/vuex/releases/tag/v3.1.1) which will definitel','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-05-07T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2810,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/139','#139 - 🇺🇸 VueConf.US 2019 talks are published; Views on Vue podcast; VueDose Tips Overload ⚡️',replace('Hello,\n\nI hope you had a great week! This week we’ve got lots of great content for you. 😃\n\nFirst, Vue Mastery has released [12 talks from the recent VueConf US](https://www.vuemastery.com/conferences/vueconf-us-2019/)! So many great presentations. Yo','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-04-30T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2811,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/138','#138 - Natalia Tepluhina joins the Vue core team! 🎉 List of probably all incoming breaking changes in Vue 3.0 and more!',replace('Hello,\n\nI’m honored to let you know that [Natalia Tepluhina](https://twitter.com/N_Tepluhina/) is now officially a Vue.js core team member! 🎉 She’s been doing an amazing job contributing to the Vue core documentation as well as several official libra','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-04-16T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2812,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/137','#137 - VueConf.TO Call for Papers; Nuxt.js v2,6 is out; 4 new RFCs for Vue! 2nd edition of VueDay in Alicante;',replace('Hello,\n\nVueConf.us was complete blast, but that’s not the only North American conference that’s worth visiting. There’s another conference called VueConf.TO in Toronto, Canada. And I heard it’s pretty amazing! It’s happening in November and if you wo','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-04-10T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2813,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/136','#136 - Vue.js Devtools 5.0 are here! 2 new Vue.js RFCs; Multiple Vue.js Amsterdam talks published; Slides from VueConf.us and more!',replace('Hey,\n\nwhat an amazing week! Just got back home from VueConf.us. It was such a great conference. Interesting presentations, amazing people and so much [fun](https://twitter.com/jenlooper/status/1111353454465830912) in general. 🦄💃\n\nAs for news: The new','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-04-01T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2814,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/135','#135 - Vue-CLI v4.0 roadmap; Nuxt.js Fetch hook RFC, Creating a Spotify-powered Vue app and more!',replace('Hello,\n\nDo you like the new Vue-CLI? Can we still call it new? Well if you do, you will probably like the incoming v4 even more, because it should open the way for plugins to run codemods when upgrading to a new version of a plugin. This should make ','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-03-19T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2815,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/134','#134 - Improvements to SSR data-fetching in Vue 2.6, first recording from Vue.js Amsterdam, how to snapshot test and more',replace('Hello!\n\nGreat news for all server-side-rendering-enthusiasts out there! With Vue v2.6 the SSR data-fetching has been rewritten and now supports "pausing" during rendering, so that additional asynchronous data can be fetched. This opens the possibilit','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-03-12T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2816,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/133','#133 - #133: New RFC: Class based API; State of Vue.js 2019 report; Getting started with Gridsome and more!',replace('Hello,\n\nhow are you doing? Evan You has published a [new request for comments](https://github.com/vuejs/rfcs/pull/17?utm_campaign=Vue.js%20News&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_source=Revue%20newsletter) regarding the introduction of native class API sup','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-03-05T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2817,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/132','#132 - Huge improvement in new Vetur release; Go and get Linusborg a coffee!; Try out hooks with Erik Hanchett',replace('Hey,\n\nI hope you’re great! I’ve got some pretty neat updates for you, especially if you’re using VS Code and Vetur. Because if you do, you have to see [the GIF in that tweet](https://twitter.com/octref/status/1097607993246416896). The tool now autosu','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-02-27T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2818,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/131','#131 - Slides from Vue.js Amsterdam; Official NativeScript support for Vue.js; Quasar 1.0.0-beta released and more!',replace('Hey!\n\nI have to tell you, Vue.js Amsterdam was a blast! 🚀 I’ve seen plenty of great talks, met lots of awesome people and had so much fun. I feel I’m still recovering from it (and the cold that I caught 🥶). Check out this [awesome Twitter thread](htt','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-02-21T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2819,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/130','#130 - Vue Storefront 1.8 released; JHipster now supports Vue; What Hooks mean for Vue?',replace('Hello!\n\nSome interesting news this week, especially if you’re also working with Java. That’s because JHipster, a development platform for developing Java apps that use modern web frameworks for their front-end has now a blueprint for Vue.js. Still in','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-02-13T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2820,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/129','#129 - Vue’s 5th aniversary! 🎆 Vue v2.6 "Macross" released! 🎉 Official Vue-CLI plugin guide and more',replace('Hello!\n\nWhat a week! 🎉\n\nThe 3rd of February was the 5th anniversary of Vue! Then the day after, on the 4th – [Vue v2.6 was officialy released](https://medium.com/the-vue-point/vue-2-6-released-66aa6c8e785e) with tons of new features. And today we are','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-02-05T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2821,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/128','#128 - #128: New releases: Vue.js v2.6.0-beta.2 and Nuxt v2.4! DYI VueVixens workshops and more!',replace('Hello,\n\ngreat news this week. New [Vue.js core library beta](https://github.com/vuejs/vue/releases/tag/v2.6.0-beta.2?utm_campaign=Vue.js%20News&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_source=Revue%20newsletter) has been released and includes some of the recentl','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-01-29T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2822,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/127','#127 - More pro-tips from Vue experts, how to make the window object properties reactive and more!',replace('Hey,\n\nif you’re interested in the RFC process of Vue 3.0 check out the [two new proposals](https://github.com/vuejs/rfcs/pulls) related to the way filters work and dynamic directive arguments.\n\nIf you think about participating in the VueConf US, you ','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-01-22T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2823,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/126','#126 - Conference news for the next 3 months; RFC process for Vue 3.0 starts now;',replace('Hey there,\n\nAs the work on Vue 3.0 goes forward we reached the point where the first of many RFCs (request for comment) has been created. The RFC process is here to provide a consistent way for introducing new features and breaking changes to the fra','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-01-15T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2824,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/125','#125 - Welcome back after the break! Check out the official Vue.js roadmap for 2019!',replace('Hello everybody!\n\nGood to be back after the holidays break. I hope you had a great time during holidays and and an awesome New Year so far! 🎉\n\nWe received plenty of submissions through our [submit-your-story](https://news.vuejs.org/submit) page (too ','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2019-01-08T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2825,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/124','#124 - Quasar 1.0 Sneak Peek; Videos from VueConf Toronto; Interview with Evan You;',replace('Hey!\n\nMore videos from VueConf Toronto are available. Check out the talks by Evan You and John Leider – the creator of Vuetify.\n\nAlso, Quasar is getting close to the 1.0 release and there are multiple new changes coming as it stabilises its API. Read','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-12-18T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2826,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/123','#123 - New patch Vue.js release; Eslint-plugin-vue 5.0 released; The program for VueConf.us is out!',replace('Hello!\n\nGreat news – Vue 2.5.18 is out now for you to use with version 2.6 underway. If you would like to check out how the works are going, provide your insight or help out, take a look at the [2.6 project board](https://github.com/vuejs/vue/project','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-12-11T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2827,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/122','#122 - Vue v2.5.18-beta.0, State of Vue.js Survey, VueConf Toronto Talks, & More','The Official Vue News Podcast (the audio version of this newsletter) has been getting funnier and funnier as Adam and I get more relaxed in front of the microphones. So, if you have a few minutes on your commute to work, mowing the lawn, or washing y','https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-12-05T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2828,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/121','#121 - Security Vulnerability found – please read the intro! @ionic/vue first alpha release and more!',replace('Hello!\n\nImportant news this week – due to a [security vulnerability](https://github.com/dominictarr/event-stream/issues/116) found in a package called __*flatmap-stream*__ it is highly recommended to reinstall the global version of Vue-CLI using thos','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-11-27T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2829,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/120','#120 - VueConf Toronto slides; New videos from Connect.tech; Preview of Vue 3.0; State of JS results and more!',replace('Hello,\n\nwhat an insane week! Tons of conference content including slides from the VueConf Toronto conference, as well as 3 new videos from Connect.Tech event from the Vue.js path.\n\nThere’s also a [great article](https://medium.com/vue-mastery/evan-yo','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-11-20T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2830,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/119','#119 - Using Vue? Evan wants to hear from you; Example repos from Chris Fritz, NativeScript 5.0 released!',replace('Hello!\n\nIf you''re with a company using Vue successfully, Evan You wants to hear from you. Core Vue Member Chris Fritz has some new resources for us: an [example monolith application](https://github.com/chrisvfritz/vue-monolith-example) and the [hello','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-11-13T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2831,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/118','#118 - Prettier now supports Vue templates! Incoming VueVixens workshops; one week until VueConf Toronto and more!',replace('Hello,\n\ngreat news – Prettier now fully supports Vue templates. 🎉This means auto-formatting for template features like v-for, slot-scope and event handlers. All thanks to the awesome work by [@ikatyang](https://github.com/ikatyang). 👏\n\nJust a week un','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-11-06T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2832,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/117','#117 - Vue-Hooks anyone? Atomic Design for Vue components; Validation Providers and more!',replace('Hello!\nRecently there’s a lot of buzz around Hooks – a new experimental addition to React, introduced by Dan Abramov a few days ago.\nEvan being Evan jumped right in on the idea and created [Vue-Hooks](https://github.com/yyx990803/vue-hooks) – a libra','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-10-30T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2833,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/116','#116 - How to build a Vue CLI plugin; Guide to writing SSR-ready components and more!',replace('Hello,\n\nDo you know the [Views on Vue](https://devchat.tv/views-on-vue/?utm_campaign=Vue.js%20News&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_source=Revue%20newsletter) podcast? In the last week episode, the guests talked about contributing to open-source. Check i','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-10-23T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2834,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/115','#115 - Q&A with the Nuxt.js creators; Introducing Gridsome – a blazing-fast static site generator with Vue and GraphQL.',replace('Hello,\n\ngreat news for all Nuxt.js fans! The Chopin brothers (Alexandre and Sebastien) will be doing a Q&amp;A session on the [Official Vue.js Chat](https://vue-land.js.org). If you got any questions for them, for example related to the recently publ','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-10-16T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2835,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/114','#114 - Let’s collect some learning materials; how to optimise your SPAs and more!',replace('Hello!\n\nFilip Rakowski from the VueStorefront team is building a [list of more advanced learning resources for Vue.js](https://github.com/filrak/vuejs-advanced-learning/blob/master/README.md). It already includes some great links so make sure to chec','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-10-09T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2836,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/113','#113 - Plans for the Vue.js 3.0 release; Both Nuxt.js and NativeScript-Vue hit the 2.0 release!',replace('Hello!\n\nHope you don’t mind the two weeks break – Vue.js London was a blast! 💥\n\nProbably the most exciting news this week – the plans for the upcoming Vue.js 3.0 release! 🔥\n\nUnless you’re into mobile development. In that case I have an even better ne','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-10-02T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2837,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/112','#112 - NativeScript support in the new Devtools beta, Nuxt.js diagrams by Krutie Patel. See you at Vue.js London!',replace('Hello,\nare you ready for Vue.js London? I’ve got a special little something for you. If you happen to be there, come and say hi! 👋\nGreat news for all NativeScript developers! The new beta.2 release of Vue.js Devtools now ships with a basic support fo','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-09-18T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2838,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/111','#111 - Sneak Peek at NativeScript-Vue 2.0; Transcription of the last two Q&A sessions with the Core Team; Learn how to build your own state management tool.',replace('Hello,\n\nit’s incredible how much momentum NativeScript-Vue is getting since the initial announcement at Vue.js Amsterdam this year. Just half a year later, Jen Looper is already talking about the [2.0 release](https://dev.to/vuevixens/a-sneak-peek-of','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-09-11T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2839,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/110','#110 - Vue.js London -50 GBP off all tickets promo code, Vue.js Devtools v5.0 beta released and more!',replace('I’m so excited – just 3 more weeks until the Vue.js London conference. The lineup looks so awesome! 😍Most of the Vue News team (Me, Gregg and Adam) will also be there so feel free to come and say hi!\n\nIn case you still haven’t made up your mind about','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-09-04T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2840,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/109','#109 - 🐉 Interview with Evan You, Vue, hits mainstream media, Vue.js version of "JavaScript 30" Challenge and more!',replace('Hello,\n\nthis week highlight: A great [interview with Evan You](https://blog.patreon.com/vue-js-creator-evan-you/) on the history and growth of Vue.\n\nIt’s also surprising (in a good way) that Vue has finally made it’s way into mainstream media in the ','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-08-28T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2841,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/108','#108 - Views on Vue, Building a 3D editor using Vue and BabylonJS and more!',replace('Hello,\nif you had the chance to meet Chris Fritz, you might have noticed he has a really good radio voice. 😅 For those that don’t know – it’s a skill he quite often utilises on the [Views on Vue podcast](https://devchat.tv/views-on-vue/) where he’s o','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-08-22T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2842,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/107','#107 - Vue CLI 3 is here! First Vue.js Sprint Summary; Vetur Roadmap and more',replace('Hey,\n\nfinally – [the Vue CLI 3.0 has been released](https://medium.com/the-vue-point/vue-cli-3-0-is-here-c42bebe28fbb)! If you still haven’t had the chance to try it – it’s about time you do.\n\nAlso, as promised – [here’s the summary from the Vue.js s','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-08-15T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2843,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/106','#106 - Updates from the Vue Sprint; Vue.js Summit in Säo Paulo, Brasil announced; VueConf TO tickets available now;',replace('Hey there,\n\nthe Vue.js Sprint has already ended – it was truly a amazing week. 8 people, 6 days, ~10h of work per day). We managed to make significant progress on several projects, most notably, but not limited to, the Vue Devtools.\n\nThere’s also an ','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-08-08T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2844,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/105','#105 - Vue.js Sprint sneak peek; Get the VueVixens Scholarship for Vue.js London!',replace('Hey,\n\nI have some great news from the front – we’re still alive and kicking! \n\nThe Vue.js Sprint is going very well and we already made significant progress on a number of tasks. Those include finishing some new eslint-plugin-vue rules, adding those ','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-07-31T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2845,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/103','#103 - 🇨🇦Vue.js Conference coming to Toronto, November 2018!',replace('Hey,\n\nI’m happy to announce that VueConf is coming to Toronto, Canada 🇨🇦, November 2018! The website is still being prepared and should launch next week along with the tickets, but you can already follow them on Twitter __[@VueToronto](https://twitte','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-07-17T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2846,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/104','#104 - Announcing Vue.js Core Team Summit #1; Vue.js Roadtrip videos;','I’m very happy to announce that along with several other Vue core team members we will be organising a free community meetup in Wrocław, Poland on Thursday next week (August 2nd). The meetup is to be called the [Vue.js Core Team Summit](https://www.m','https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-07-24T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2847,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/102','#102 - First look into Vue UI, New Vue.js London conference speakers and more',replace('Hey!\n\nVue.js London conference has announced several new talks – you can check the speakers list [here](https://vuejs.london/schedule). Additionally, VueVixens will be running a two free half-day workshops among other workshops that happen a day befo','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-07-10T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2848,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/101','#101 - Vue.js Roadtrip Paris slides, Vue-Storefront release 1.0 is here and more!','A great week for the Vue ecosystem! [Vue-Storefront](https://www.vuestorefront.io/), the largest eCommerce-related Vue open-source project I know about, [has hit the 1.0 version](https://medium.com/@piotrkarwatka/vue-storefront-1-0-1e6c9cfe8075). Thi','https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-07-03T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2849,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/100','#100 - Vue.js London Tickets and Date! Build your own reactivity system with Proxies and more!',replace('In case you haven’t noticed, this is the 100th issue! 🎉\n\nIt means we’re doing this for around 700 days now! And since last week, we passed the 10,000 subscribers mark! It has been an awesome journey so far and I’m extremely grateful to everyone invol','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-06-26T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2850,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/99','#99 - Vue-Land’s 1st anniversary! Vue-CLI has now a modern-mode',replace('Hey,\n\ndo you know that Vue has a Discord server called Vue-Land? Do you know that this particular server just had its first anniversary? If you don’t, go to [chat.vuejs.org](https://chat.vuejs.org) and join the 35000 users from all over the world. It','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-06-19T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2851,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/98','#98 - Vue Contributor Days Stream; Interview with Evan You, Vue.js London is coming!',replace('Hey! \n\nIf you watched the recent [Vue Contributor Day stream](https://www.youtube.com/watch?utm_campaign=Revue+newsletter&amp;utm_medium=Newsletter&amp;utm_source=Vue.js+News&amp;v=U38s3O1hh9k) you might have already learnt that our webpage has becom','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-06-12T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2852,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/97','#97 - Vue.js Meetups, Vue Contributor Day, Vue-CLI UI in the latest beta release and more!',replace('I can’t believe I only now learned about [VueMeetups.org](https://vuemeetups.org) – a very nice initiative by Ben Hong. It’s the biggest list of Vue meetups around the world that I have ever seen. Try it out, you might just find one near you.\n\nAlso, ','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-06-05T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2853,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/96','#96 - Reminder: One week left until Vue Contributor Day! Slides from Vue.js Roadtrip Barcelona; Announcing Saber.js and more...',replace('If you’re interested in contributing to the Vue ecosystem, better start planning your schedule for next Wednesday because [Vue Contributor Day](https://www.thisdot.co/events/attend-vue-contributor-days) is just around the corner.\n\n[EGOIST](https://gi','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-05-29T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(2854,'https://news.vuejs.org/issues/95','#95 - Build native desktop apps using Vuido (without Electron), Vue design decisions discussed and more!',replace('I just learned about [Vuido](https://github.com/mimecorg/vuido) – a fork of Vue that makes it possible to create native desktop applications without the need for Electron. 🔥\nUnderneath it uses libui, a GUI library written in C. Though it’s still in i','\n',char(10)),'https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2018-05-22T00:00:00','Vue Official','Frontend');
