INSERT INTO news VALUES(3770,'https://www.architecture-weekly.com/p/on-rebuilding-read-models-dead-letter','On rebuilding read models, Dead-Letter Queues and Why Letting Go is Sometimes the Answer','In the last article, I explained how to rebuild Event-Driven Read Models in a safe and resilient way. I asked readers to let me know if they find any blind spots in my design.','https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!jBdJ!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F247ed8c5-16a9-4d5a-93cd-01077982a5a7_800x500.png','2026-01-19T18:01:47','Architecture Weekly','System Design');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(3771,'https://www.architecture-weekly.com/p/rebuilding-event-driven-read-models','Rebuilding Event-Driven Read Models in a safe and resilient way','And what distributed locking, PostgreSQL Advisory Locks have to do with that','https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!9xrQ!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F75073730-6b26-4f4a-ac3e-74b77d704aee_800x500.png','2026-01-05T19:01:10','Architecture Weekly','System Design');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(3772,'https://www.architecture-weekly.com/p/architecture-weekly-is-5-years-old','Architecture Weekly is 5 years old! 🎉','Yup, I just realised that it happened! Let''s do a small celebration and recap how I got here!','https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!SC8-!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F50caeedf-229d-41f2-a0c5-0f1ddec01669_3088x2316.jpeg','2025-12-29T10:40:08','Architecture Weekly','System Design');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(3773,'https://www.architecture-weekly.com/p/multi-tenancy-and-dynamic-messaging','Multi-tenancy and dynamic messaging workload distribution','This time, I discussed how to setup and scale message processing when you have multi-tenant environment or other dynamic setup. You''ll see considerations where to scale horizontally, where vertically and why that matters to you','https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!XKNu!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F61c397bb-090d-4464-be3d-b52f5fa3e483_800x640.png','2025-12-15T15:50:13','Architecture Weekly','System Design');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(3774,'https://www.architecture-weekly.com/p/checkpointing-the-message-processing','Checkpointing the message processing','I realised that checkpointing our (message) processing is similar to using cheat codes in Super Frog and similar old games.We need to recover and use the code to get where we were. Of course, sometimes that means going through the half of the level a','https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!PhAK!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1ec7cb38-3378-4779-9848-eed89246e8c0_800x500.png','2025-12-08T15:15:49','Architecture Weekly','System Design');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(3775,'https://www.architecture-weekly.com/p/consumers-projectors-reactors-and','Consumers, projectors, reactors and all that messaging jazz in Emmett','Let me show you today how I designed messaging abstractions in Emmett, and why I split them into Consumers and Processors. Why I added abstractions like Projector and Reactor, and the trade-offs I chose. I think this can be a good learning experience','https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!OVgV!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc97019ab-3f11-42d6-8915-eb69b57024a0_800x683.jpeg','2025-12-01T16:02:26','Architecture Weekly','System Design');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(3776,'https://www.architecture-weekly.com/p/requeuing-roulette-in-event-driven','Requeuing Roulette in Event-Driven Architecture and Messaging','I&#8217;m always saying that there&#8217;s a thin line between good and bad practice, and this thin line is named &#8220;Context&#8221;. That&#8217;s also true for the (anti-)pattern I&#8217;m calling &#8220;Requeuing Roulette&#8221;.What&#8217;s the','https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!i9BO!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc271ef58-6806-4fa6-8d18-aa01e1556bd8_800x356.png','2025-11-17T18:35:13','Architecture Weekly','System Design');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(3777,'https://www.architecture-weekly.com/p/handling-events-coming-in-an-unknown','Handling Events Coming in an Unknown Order','In the last article we discussed on the scenario where you know what events you should receive, just not the order. But what if you don''t know that? That''s the question I got from Ben, let''s answer that today and explain how using revisions can help ','https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!ppfN!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8b7fa258-9208-478a-8c61-a48a531b9f11_626x391.png','2025-11-03T20:04:01','Architecture Weekly','System Design');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(3778,'https://www.architecture-weekly.com/p/dealing-with-race-conditions-in-event','Dealing with Race Conditions in Event-Driven Architecture with Read Models','My events came out of order! What should I do? Are you familiar with the term "phantom record" and its benefits? No? Let me explain it to you today. Let''s discuss how to embrace the chaos and learn to deal with it.','https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!Nf89!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8e700ce6-5b15-42dd-8766-50d324343a24_626x391.png','2025-10-20T18:02:36','Architecture Weekly','System Design');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(3779,'https://www.architecture-weekly.com/p/on-messaging-and-distributed-systems','On Messaging and Distributed Systems with Ian Cooper','Why do we still need to learn messaging? Why isn&#8217;t it a commodity yet? How to shape boundaries, and how data on the insight, and data on the outside can help in that. This and more we discussed with Ian Cooper learning also how he started his j','https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2025-10-13T05:01:59','Architecture Weekly','System Design');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(3780,'https://www.architecture-weekly.com/p/new-recording-on-event-modelling','New Recording on Event modelling anti-patterns from DDDEU','Have you heard about Passive Aggressive Events or CRUD sourcing? Or maybe about the Clickbait event?If you don''t, check the recording of my talk, as knowing only best practices is one side of the coin. Knowing what NOT to do can be even more importan','https://via.placeholder.com/400x250?text=Tech+News','2025-10-06T09:01:30','Architecture Weekly','System Design');
INSERT INTO news VALUES(3781,'https://www.architecture-weekly.com/p/sneaky-code-bites-back','Sneaky Code Bites Back','I was adding SQLite support to Pongo when I realised that I''m talking to myself, and what I heard was insane. I was trying to understand and recap what I just built, an extremely clever and sneaky solution to handle multiple databases. I realised I w','https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!ps3C!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff2c15624-c7ec-4bc5-b4de-0fc4851db328_780x438.jpeg','2025-09-22T12:05:28','Architecture Weekly','System Design');
